tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE SolarPowerData (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    solar_power_generation DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE historical_solar_power_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    generation_amount DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE weather_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    temperature DECIMAL,
    precipitation DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE location_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    city VARCHAR,
    state VARCHAR,
    country VARCHAR
)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    birthdate DATE
)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS installations (
    installation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    capacity DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    start_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS solar_panels (
    panel_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    installation_id INT NOT NULL,
    brand VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    series VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    efficiency DECIMAL(5,2)
)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS solar_generation (
    generation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    panel_id INT NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    time TIME NOT NULL,
    power_generated DECIMAL(8,2) NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS weather (
    date DATE PRIMARY KEY,
    temperature DECIMAL(5,2) NOT NULL,
    humidity DECIMAL(5,2) NOT NULL,
    precipitation DECIMAL(5,2)
)
